<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=51&amp;p=256#p256"><![CDATA[
Don't forget to make sure you're not using any of the RAM used by the NSF for your game.  Plus I'd imagine MCK music isn't very optimized for game playback... so it'll likely eat up a lot of CPU time.  You might want to  consider working on your own music engine.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=33">Disch</a> — Tue Nov 23, 2004 9:02 pm</p><hr />
