<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=51&amp;p=253#p253"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Putting NSF into code]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=51&amp;p=253#p253"><![CDATA[
Yeah, first you need to get 3 things from the NSF file.<br /><br />1.  Load address, where in memory you put the actual NSF file (remember to either strip the 128-byte NSF header off, or subtract 128 from the load address).<br /><br />2.  Init address.  Load A with the song #, and JSR to this to set stuff up (MCK only supports one song though, AFAIK).<br /><br />3.  Play address, JSR to it 60 times a second (like the the nmi routine).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=10">Memblers</a> — Tue Nov 23, 2004 8:28 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
